post_text:
Dear teachers,
My life has been altered quite a bit from the coronavirus. Sports have been canceled which I was really looking forward to. School is now online, which is going alright but it’s just not the same. I really wish we could go back to school because teachers can then explain things and you can ask them questions in person. Also, I won’t get to finish my 8th-grade year in school, and we can’t take pictures at the end of the school year. Almost everything is closed and we have to stay home. It’s just boring having every day even the weekends be exactly the same. My level of appreciation for life as we used to know it has gone up tremendously. I’ve learned to not take things for granted and to appreciate everything we have. In the blink of an eye, everything can change so just appreciate everything you have and are able to do is what I’ve mainly learned from this.

Sincerely,
Sarah Geiseman

post_text: Show your support for our student-athletes - The coronavirus pandemic has brought many aspects of life to a halt, including athletics and other extra-curricular activities. To shine a light on all of those students that are missing out not only on their activities, but also their school time with friends and teachers, Lena-Winslow will participate in the "Be The Light" movement. To show our support for all those students affected, the lights at the Lena-Winslow HS Football Field will be turned on tonight, April 10 at 8PM for 1 Hour. Our scoreboard will be lit up to display support for this year's class of 2020. We remind anyone that happens to come by the field to remain in your vehicle and to observe social distancing. http://edne.tw/n629270

post_text:
Butterbraid Orders Due March 16 - Music students still have a few days left to offer family, friends and neighbors the once-in-a-year opportunity to purchase the divinely delectable pastry creation known as the “Butter Braid.”



“From sinfully sticky caramel rolls to heavenly cream cheese and strawberry braids to the new option of cinnamon rolls, the selection will have mouths watering across the community,” said Diane Fiedler, Butter Braid Fundraiser Chair.



Folks wishing to ensure a music student swings by their home can email musicboosters@le-win.net with their phone number and address or call Diane at 815-275-6607. Those who know a Le-Win jr. high or high school music student are welcome to request them by name. Delivery is scheduled for March 31.

http://edne.tw/n618707

5Essentials Survey Link - To all Lena-Winslow parents:

It is the time of year that we ask for your feedback regarding your child(ren)'s school(s). The 5Essentials Survey is a tool that was developed and is administered by the University of Chicago and is a statewide initiative. The different data sets produced by parents, students, and educators is very valuable to the school district. The survey is completely anonymous and will take 5 - 10 minutes to complete. I would greatly appreciate if you would take the time to do so. Your input is highly valued and is one of the main pieces of information that the district uses to make changes and improvements.

As always, I greatly appreciate your involvement in your child(ren)'s education(s).

Sincerely,
Tom Chiles
Superintendent http://edne.tw/n602166

post_text: Pete Brown selected to ITCCCA Hall of Fame - Longtime Lena-Winslow track coach Pete Brown has been selected by the Illinois Track and Cross Country Coaches Association for induction into the Hall of Fame. Pete Brown was the track coach at Lena-Winslow from 1979-2013, winning numerous conference championships, and finishing 2nd in the state at the 1993 Boys State Meet. The induction will be held on January 11 in the Chicago suburbs. For more information contact Activities Director Tom Smargiassi at smargiassit@le-win.net. http://edne.tw/n596223

If you want to order a shirt and help us reach our goal, let us know. Orders are due November 1 to Mrs. Schultz. The order form is attached. http://edne.tw/n595021

post_text: High School Winter Sports Parent Meeting - There will be a mandatory meeting for the parents of any HS athlete planning to participate in winter athletics during the 2019-2020 season. The meeting will be held on Monday November 4th at 6:30 in the HS gym. Attendance by at least one parent is required prior to any athlete being allowed to participate. The purpose of the meeting is to create communication between parents, athletes, and the coaches of our various athletic programs. The meeting should not take longer than one hour. If you have questions feel free to contact Tom Smargiassi, Activities Director at 815-291-5362 or smargiassit@le-win.net http://edne.tw/n592894

post_text: FFA Greenhand Conference - On Tuesday October 8th, 10 Greenhands (First year FFA Members) form Lena-Winslow traveled to Highland Community College to take part in the Greenhand Conference where they participated in workshops ranging from mini judging contests to team building. Also, three Lena-Winslow FFA officers helped to facilitate the workshops and conference. Greenhands Pictured left to Right ( Back Row: Andrew Kempel, Maisen Smith, Jace Flynn, Nehemiha Schroeder, Curtis Story, AJ Phillips, and Sam Peceraro. Front Row: Isabella Forbes, Taylor Robinson, and Emma kempel.) Officers Pictured Left to right (Sarah Foley, Samantha Kempel, and Braden Baldauf) http://edne.tw/n592701

post_text:
Applications Being Accepted for Building and Grounds Director - Lena-Winslow CUSD #202 has an opening for a Full-time Building and Grounds Director and is looking for a knowledgeable applicant in maintenance and operations. Experience in being responsible for building maintenance, electrical/HVAC, grounds & landscaping, custodial services, and construction. Demonstrates organization and professionalism in fulfilling the responsibilities of the position. The position is in continual contact with supervision, administrative leadership, work crews, and outside contractors.

Please submit resume with references to Tom Chiles, Superintendent, Le-Win Schools, 401 Fremont St., Lena, IL, 61048 or by email to chilest@le-win.net. Applications will be accepted until October 25, 2019.

http://edne.tw/n592479

post_text:
Homecoming Parade Change - Mother nature is not cooperating! Based on tomorrow's weather forecast, we have made the decision to postpone the parade until Friday, October 4. Lineup will be at Lion's Park at 1:45pm and the parade will start at 2:00pm. The parade will end on Fremont St. in front of the High School at approximately 3:00pm.

Iron Man Volleyball for Wednesday night is still on! The juniors and seniors will play each other at 7pm with the winner taking on the undefeated teacher team.

On Friday, October 4, we will crown the 2019 Homecoming King and Queen before the varsity game.

Homecoming dance tickets are on sale in the office for $5. Students should pay for tickets before school, during lunch, or after school. Out of town guest registration forms are due on Thursday, October 3 at 3:30PM. http://edne.tw/n590942

post_text: 2020 Band & Chorus Summer Trip Meeting - Join us on Thursday, September 26th at 7pm in the elementary cafeteria.This informational meeting is open to all parents and music students, grades 8 and up, who are interested in learning more about the 2020 Summer Music Trip to Atlanta. A representative from Vanguard Tours will be on hand to discuss the trip and answer any questions families may have. While the initial deadline for deposit was Sept. 16, late registration is available to students who are undecided and want to learn more about the trip first. “We hope to see this meeting generate an increase in participation for this trip to proceed as planned. This meeting presents a great opportunity for parents and students who are already committed and those who are still on the fence,” said Renee Schultz, band instructor. http://edne.tw/n589492
